<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1749,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,655,1749,1776]" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Substratum, ecology and depth range.</emphasis>
The sponge was found growing attached on the stem of a submerged water plant (macrophyte) (
<taxonomicName box="[453,602,1786,1811]" class="Liliopsida" family="Potamogetonaceae" genus="Potamogeton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="3" pageNumber="366" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[453,602,1786,1811]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Potamogeton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.). Only one specimen was seen, growing just beyond the outer margin of the emergent plant zone. Water in the lake very clear, but sometimes there is a brown stain. Lake protected from the wind and hence not much exposed to wave action. Collected at a depth between 
<quantity box="[1094,1168,1858,1884]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="366" unit="m" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">
1– 
<specimenCount box="[1120,1168,1858,1884]" pageId="3" pageNumber="366" type="generic">2 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
