<emphasis box="[461,580,1966,1992]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">P. weltneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
share similar megascleres and microscleres with the new species. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Levi" authorityYear="1965" box="[151,291,2002,2028]" class="Demospongiae" family="Potamolepidae" genus="Potamolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="3" pageNumber="366" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="belingana">
<emphasis box="[151,291,2002,2028]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">P. belingana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burton" authorityYear="1938" box="[304,439,2002,2028]" class="Demospongiae" family="Potamolepidae" genus="Potamolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="3" pageNumber="366" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="marshalli">
<emphasis box="[304,439,2002,2028]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">P. marshalli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burton" authorityYear="1938" box="[453,597,2002,2027]" class="Demospongiae" family="Potamolepidae" genus="Potamolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="3" pageNumber="366" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="micropora">
<emphasis box="[453,597,2002,2027]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">P. micropora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="1883" box="[651,774,2002,2028]" class="Demospongiae" family="Potamolepidae" genus="Potamolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="3" pageNumber="366" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="pechueli">
<emphasis box="[651,774,2002,2028]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">P. pechueli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have acanthoxea microscleres compared to the presence of microscleres strongyles in the new species. Based on a number of spicular congruencies, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="1883" box="[1136,1268,153,179]" class="Demospongiae" family="Potamolepidae" genus="Potamolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="chartaria">
<emphasis box="[1136,1268,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">P. chartaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Pinheiro &amp; Calheira &amp; Martins &amp; Janson &amp; Taylor &amp; Samaai, 2020" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Calheira &amp; Martins &amp; Janson &amp; Taylor &amp; Samaai" authorityYear="2020" box="[179,310,189,215]" class="Demospongiae" family="Potamolepidae" genus="Potamolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="bhangazi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[179,310,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">P. bhangazi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[316,405,189,215]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[316,405,189,215]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="1883" box="[411,664,189,215]" class="Demospongiae" family="Potamolepidae" genus="Potamolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="chartaria">
<emphasis box="[411,664,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">Potamolepis chartaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
however, have either smooth or spiny strongyle megascleres with inflated tips; in contrast to the tips found in 
<taxonomicName authority="Pinheiro &amp; Calheira &amp; Martins &amp; Janson &amp; Taylor &amp; Samaai, 2020" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Calheira &amp; Martins &amp; Janson &amp; Taylor &amp; Samaai" authorityYear="2020" box="[608,737,225,251]" class="Demospongiae" family="Potamolepidae" genus="Potamolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="bhangazi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[608,737,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">P. bhangazi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[742,830,225,251]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[742,830,225,251]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, which is mucronate and always smooth. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName authority="Pinheiro &amp; Calheira &amp; Martins &amp; Janson &amp; Taylor &amp; Samaai, 2020" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Calheira &amp; Martins &amp; Janson &amp; Taylor &amp; Samaai" authorityYear="2020" box="[151,282,261,287]" class="Demospongiae" family="Potamolepidae" genus="Potamolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="bhangazi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,282,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">P. bhangazi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[288,378,261,287]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[288,378,261,287]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has larger microscleres than those found in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="1883" box="[872,1005,261,287]" class="Demospongiae" family="Potamolepidae" genus="Potamolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="chartaria">
<emphasis box="[872,1005,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">P. chartaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
